WEBVTT

00:04.642 --> 00:16.317
Last week we began a new series called Life Matters and what we've been talking within that series is about the matters of life and the matters of the mission.

00:17.098 --> 00:23.486
Like we are on this planet because as followers of Jesus because our job is not done.

00:24.167 --> 00:33.298
We could worship better in heaven, we could be with God better in heaven, we could do all those things better if we were in His presence but we're here still here for a reason and that reason, that mission

00:33.474 --> 00:37.578
We state it this way is to help people find and follow Jesus.

00:37.618 --> 00:47.769
And so what we're gonna do over these five weeks and we started last week is we're gonna find some tools to put in our toolbox to accomplish that mission.

00:48.009 --> 00:50.351
Okay, I'm supposed to help people find and follow Jesus.

00:50.411 --> 00:51.372
How do I do that?

00:51.392 --> 00:54.876
What are the things I need to be equipped with to do that?

00:54.896 --> 00:57.659
And the first one we looked at last week is we need to know what truth is.

00:58.259 --> 00:59.460
We have to know what truth is.

00:59.500 --> 01:01.042
The truth is not a concept.

01:01.186 --> 01:05.552
The truth is not just some piffy sayings by some wise men and women.

01:05.612 --> 01:14.365
Truth we found out last week is the character of God and the person and work of Jesus.

01:15.026 --> 01:28.946
There are a bunch of things that are true, but what we get to tell people about isn't just we go to church, isn't just we listen to Christian music, isn't just we wear Jesus t-shirts, isn't just that we have verses tattooed on the back of our arm,

01:29.826 --> 01:40.161
We get to tell people about the character and person and work of Jesus because that's what they need to hear about, not our Christian things, right?

01:40.622 --> 01:43.326
And so Pilate asked Jesus, what is truth?

01:43.446 --> 01:47.853
And he responded basically with, well, the better question is who is truth?

01:48.714 --> 01:49.475
Who is truth?

01:49.956 --> 01:54.162
And then today we're going to look at something that I think is vital.

01:55.106 --> 01:56.828
to helping people find and follow Jesus.

01:56.868 --> 02:04.417
And I don't think it would end up on a lot of people's list, but man, it sure should be and we see it in Jesus over and over and over.

02:04.437 --> 02:08.562
It's this idea of proximity and empathy.

02:09.283 --> 02:21.778
And here's why that's the tool that needs to be in your toolbox, Christian, is because we cannot, I believe we cannot effectively make kingdom ripples from a distance.

02:22.946 --> 02:25.450
And so if you're wondering like, man, what does proximity mean?

02:25.510 --> 02:26.772
Here's proximity, right?

02:26.792 --> 02:30.658
Like right now I'm at distance from my friend Kent, right?

02:31.619 --> 02:37.749
If I wasn't, and I'm gonna get closer to him than he wants a Bears Jersey to ever be as a Packers fan, good to see you bro, touch that, yeah.

02:38.710 --> 02:40.433
Now I'm in proximity, right?

02:41.094 --> 02:42.115
Now I'm in proximity.

02:42.255 --> 02:43.918
So that's what proximity is.

02:43.938 --> 02:46.642
It's just getting in close enough

02:47.138 --> 02:47.859
to have empathy.

02:47.979 --> 02:53.928
My favorite quote on this matter is by Tyler Merritt in a book he wrote called, I Take My Coffee Black.

02:54.269 --> 02:55.851
You should read it if you haven't.

02:55.871 --> 03:04.004
But he says this, distance breeds suspicion, but proximity breeds empathy.

03:05.386 --> 03:13.458
You see, it is really, really easy if you're sitting on this side of the room to have suspicion about someone on that side of the room.

03:14.338 --> 03:14.578
Right?

03:14.598 --> 03:17.762
Someone on that side of the room, it could look like they are dozing off.

03:17.782 --> 03:18.623
It better not be yet.

03:18.644 --> 03:19.885
I just got started, wake up.

03:20.206 --> 03:22.488
Or you could be looking at them and saying, man, look at that.

03:22.528 --> 03:24.030
Or I know this about that person.

03:24.070 --> 03:25.512
Or, man, they're sitting this way.

03:25.572 --> 03:27.335
Or whatever you watch them from afar.

03:27.535 --> 03:30.298
Distance allows you to have suspicion.

03:30.318 --> 03:31.580
It's why the news is dangerous.

03:31.600 --> 03:32.762
Social media is dangerous.

03:33.102 --> 03:34.103
All those kind of things.

03:34.263 --> 03:40.552
It is really, really easy to look far away and be like, hmm, I wonder what their angle is.

03:42.314 --> 03:42.514
All right.

03:44.226 --> 04:09.618
It's really easy to say a bunch of things from a distance, but when we get in proximity, if you walked across the room and you got close and you listened to a story and you found out what's going on, almost always you start to have empathy because now you've grown closer to see what's there.

04:09.922 --> 04:11.384
Harper Lee describes it this way.

04:11.444 --> 04:21.078
You never really understand a person until you consider things from his or her point of view until you climb into his skin and walk around in it.

04:22.340 --> 04:28.129
You know why this sticks out to me and why it struck me when I read it Tuesday studying was this is what God did.

04:29.250 --> 04:30.492
It's exactly what God did.

04:30.552 --> 04:37.202
God climbed into our skin and then walked around in the person of Jesus.

04:37.570 --> 04:37.891
Right?

04:37.931 --> 04:45.385
The word became flesh and dwelt among us, John says, so that he could come close in proximity.

04:45.625 --> 04:55.684
He climbed into our skin to see what we see from the angle that we see it, to feel what we feel firsthand, not just from a distant third heaven.

04:55.964 --> 04:59.090
And he was, as we know from scripture, tempted

04:59.426 --> 05:04.251
As we were tempted, Hebrews, chapter four, verse 15 describes it so well about God's proximity.

05:04.532 --> 05:10.758
He says, we do not have a high priest speaking of Jesus who is unable to sympathize with our weaknesses.

05:11.419 --> 05:13.161
How does God know what I'm going through?

05:13.201 --> 05:14.463
How does God understand?

05:14.483 --> 05:15.023
He's God.

05:15.043 --> 05:15.584
He's perfect.

05:15.604 --> 05:16.285
He's so far.

05:16.345 --> 05:17.686
He doesn't live in puree.

05:17.746 --> 05:18.607
He can't fathom it.

05:20.389 --> 05:23.132
Oh, he can because he did.

05:24.954 --> 05:28.498
He says, but one who in every respect, not just some,

05:29.090 --> 05:33.416
has been tempted as we are, yet without sin.

05:34.438 --> 05:47.316
Alfred Adler said, empathy is seeing with the eyes of another, listening with the ears of another, and feeling with the heart of another.

05:47.917 --> 05:57.330
And if you go through the gospels, Matthew, Mark, Luke, John, and even go into the book of Acts, what you will see is this is exactly why Jesus

05:57.602 --> 06:00.726
did the things he did and the way he did them, right?

06:01.207 --> 06:07.455
So that he could have the eyes of another, so that he could have the listening of another, so he could have the feeling of another, just think about it.

06:08.016 --> 06:11.721
That's why he touched the leper and just didn't heal him, right?

06:11.741 --> 06:18.550
He touched the leper, who cannot be touched, who should be put out of the assembly, should not be, any, it should be quarantined.

06:19.632 --> 06:21.234
And he touched him to heal him.

06:22.082 --> 06:25.567
He sat with Peter on the shoreline after Peter denied him three times.

06:25.627 --> 06:33.838
And not only did he sit with him on the shoreline and enjoy a meal with him, but he also said things to him three times.

06:34.359 --> 06:36.622
He asked him, do you love me three times?

06:36.702 --> 06:39.385
He told him to feed my sheep, feed my lambs three times.

06:40.407 --> 06:43.431
He drew close in proximity.

06:44.272 --> 06:50.340
He washed the feet of his disciples, not through a servant, but through his own hands.

06:50.861 --> 06:51.602
He knelt.

06:52.450 --> 06:53.772
He girded his loins.

06:53.912 --> 06:55.394
He carried the basin.

06:55.875 --> 06:56.676
He washed it.

06:56.957 --> 06:57.638
Even Judas.

06:58.499 --> 06:59.340
He washed his feet.

06:59.941 --> 07:05.148
And he took upon our sin, not upon someone else, but upon himself.

07:05.689 --> 07:06.711
And here's the thing.

07:06.871 --> 07:09.595
Jesus showed us to do the mission.

07:09.955 --> 07:15.744
You have to have proximity and empathy in your toolbox.

07:15.764 --> 07:16.525
And here's the truth.

07:17.386 --> 07:20.050
We can be just like Jesus.

07:20.610 --> 07:24.756
if we get close enough to others to feel.

07:26.018 --> 07:29.764
If we get, Jesus got close enough to feel, and he tells us to do the same thing.

07:30.085 --> 07:37.937
One of the examples is in Romans 12, verse 15, he says, rejoice with those who rejoice and weep with those who weep.

07:39.579 --> 07:49.234
He said, I want you to get close enough to feel what they're feeling, to feel they're rejoicing, to feel they're weeping,

07:50.018 --> 08:00.170
See, because here's what can happen when we allow ourselves to feel what others feel, we begin to see them not as issues to solve, but as people to love.

08:00.190 --> 08:02.052
And let me just encourage you with that.

08:02.092 --> 08:08.439
If you are going to do the mission of Jesus, if you want to go help people find and follow Jesus, they cannot be a project.

08:09.440 --> 08:10.942
They cannot because they know.

08:11.002 --> 08:13.385
They know if you have an angle.

08:14.106 --> 08:16.468
They know if you have an agenda, right?

08:16.489 --> 08:17.810
If you start to,

08:18.018 --> 08:39.289
get in people's lives and you think, man, I'm just gonna draw in proximity so that I can hook them into coming to church and I can Jesus juke them into believing in the gospel and then I can Holy Spirit, personal Holy Spirit convict them and shame them into the baptism tank, then maybe they'll become the people that God wants them to become and no one responds to that.

08:39.510 --> 08:40.831
No one wants to be a project.

08:40.952 --> 08:42.394
Everyone wants to be a person.

08:43.916 --> 08:45.298
Everyone wants to be a person.

08:45.666 --> 08:48.450
And you know when someone feels what you feel.

08:48.490 --> 08:55.238
And you know when someone sees you, not just sees you as a project.

08:55.839 --> 09:09.156
Now I believe in this verse in Romans chapter 12 verse 15, I believe strongly that the first one, rejoicing with those who rejoice is much harder for us, especially in the household of God.

09:09.757 --> 09:14.002
I think we actually don't mind and do the weep with those who weep pretty well.

09:14.210 --> 09:18.214
And you know why, here's why I think, because weeping with those who weep makes us feel good.

09:20.077 --> 09:21.018
It makes us feel good.

09:21.778 --> 09:24.702
Someone loses a loved one like, man, we run right to that.

09:24.782 --> 09:26.684
There's tragedy, we run right to that, right?

09:27.985 --> 09:35.734
We're like, man, because we're serving them and we're with them when we show them how selfless we are, even though we're making us feel good, right?

09:35.754 --> 09:41.060
It's the first one, rejoice with those who rejoice that I think is really hard.

09:42.281 --> 09:42.962
And here's why.

09:44.450 --> 09:52.540
Rejoicing for others is the selfless act of celebrating someone else's blessing, not yours.

09:54.803 --> 10:04.856
It's so hard to celebrate someone else's blessing, especially if you struggle to remember your blessings.

10:05.697 --> 10:08.821
Let me give you a personal example of when I failed at this horribly.

10:09.762 --> 10:12.626
Many moons ago, I lived in Kansas City, Kansas,

10:12.706 --> 10:15.369
That's why my son is a Kansas City Chiefs fan.

10:15.409 --> 10:20.575
And that's why we rooted for the Royals when they won the World Series and best barbecue on the planet.

10:20.615 --> 10:21.556
Hands down Memphis.

10:21.576 --> 10:22.097
You're wrong.

10:22.357 --> 10:23.799
Like we love Kansas City.

10:23.839 --> 10:24.419
We loved it.

10:24.680 --> 10:26.782
And we have friends there that were friends in Ohio.

10:26.802 --> 10:29.145
They were close, close friends, still are friends to this day.

10:29.485 --> 10:31.227
And their names were Kevin and Meagan Alexander.

10:31.287 --> 10:32.709
And they lived about 10 minutes from us.

10:32.769 --> 10:33.750
Went to the same church.

10:34.171 --> 10:40.658
And I remember Kevin and I were talking and he told me about yesterday my parents gave us

10:40.802 --> 10:43.125
a Honda van for free.

10:44.466 --> 10:46.008
And we both had young kids at the time.

10:46.048 --> 10:49.633
Luke and Ethan were really young, and he and his young boys were the same as mine.

10:49.653 --> 10:52.256
He had two, and we were pretty poor.

10:53.517 --> 10:54.278
We were pretty poor.

10:54.338 --> 10:55.099
Things were struggling.

10:55.119 --> 10:56.461
We hadn't owned our first home yet.

10:56.761 --> 11:10.578
And I remember talking to my wife, and I remember thinking, where's my free van, yo?

11:11.202 --> 11:16.128
The Ultimate Beer Larrow is not quite big enough for the crew, you know?

11:16.148 --> 11:18.651
Like, where's the van at?

11:18.671 --> 11:20.974
Must be nice to have parents hook you up with a free van.

11:24.939 --> 11:29.324
Now, if tragedy had hit Kevin and Meagan, I'd be at their house day and night until they needed it.

11:30.806 --> 11:34.350
And publicly with Kevin and Meagan, I was like, dude, that's so awesome!

11:35.572 --> 11:38.295
I'm sorry, I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

11:38.315 --> 11:39.356
I even think he deserved it.

11:39.997 --> 11:40.658
Hi, Kevin.

11:40.738 --> 11:46.144
I know he'll watch now because that doesn't mean.

11:46.164 --> 11:55.795
We see it so hard until we get in proximity to people to rejoice with those who rejoice.

11:57.156 --> 12:00.300
Philippians chapter two, verse three says, here's why we should.

12:00.400 --> 12:05.145
It says, do nothing from selfish ambition or conceit, but in humility, listen these words.

12:05.926 --> 12:09.650
Count others more significant.

12:10.530 --> 12:15.379
than yourselves.

12:15.399 --> 12:15.479
Wow.

12:15.499 --> 12:22.613
How can I begin to rejoice with those who rejoice to the point where I get in close proximity to them?

12:22.893 --> 12:25.999
And I feel their joy from this blessing.

12:26.300 --> 12:30.368
And I think where God wants us to grow is grow to the place where you're happier.

12:30.428 --> 12:33.714
They got the blessing than you would be if you got it yourself.

12:36.034 --> 12:40.421
Because man, I place Kevin and Meagan more important than myself.

12:40.722 --> 12:43.546
So I'm so glad they got the van and not us.

12:44.528 --> 12:46.070
It's not where I was in my faith.

12:47.513 --> 12:55.205
One Corinthians chapter 10 verse 24 says, let no one seek his own good, but the good of his neighbor.

12:57.148 --> 13:03.058
And we will do that when we get close enough to feel.

13:04.258 --> 13:07.883
If you could feel they're rejoicing, it would make you rejoice.

13:07.923 --> 13:12.028
But from a distance, it's just somebody else who got something that you didn't get.

13:13.790 --> 13:16.814
It's when we tell someone, hey, I think you've grieved long enough.

13:18.296 --> 13:20.358
Never tell someone how long they need to grieve.

13:21.460 --> 13:26.466
Get in proximity close enough to feel what they feel and say, you take the time you need.

13:26.586 --> 13:28.528
I'm here, right?

13:28.548 --> 13:33.074
Job's friend sat with him in ashes for a few days and then said, okay, buddy, boy, it's enough.

13:33.730 --> 13:34.471
What'd you do wrong?

13:36.154 --> 13:38.117
They didn't get close enough in proximity.

13:38.718 --> 13:41.943
Now, there's some good questions to ask yourself that we're going to encourage you to ask this morning.

13:41.963 --> 13:43.285
Here's a few things you could ask.

13:43.305 --> 13:46.430
Am I close enough to feel their celebration or hurt?

13:47.351 --> 13:51.297
Am I close enough to feel that person's celebration hurt or do I need to give it more time?

13:51.978 --> 13:54.101
Am I still too far away to understand?

13:54.382 --> 13:56.064
Do I need to put some prayer into that?

13:56.104 --> 13:57.867
Do I need to put some connection into that?

13:59.450 --> 14:02.354
You can ask, have I taken the time to listen process?

14:02.498 --> 14:03.740
and say, tell me more.

14:04.521 --> 14:12.031
We said this weeks and weeks ago when I did a demonstration up here with a bucket and a well, like, have you dropped your bucket into the heart of that person?

14:12.732 --> 14:21.384
Have you let your bucket down into the well of their heart and said, let me pull out all that's going on so that I can grow in my empathy for their situation?

14:22.145 --> 14:28.434
And then one of the questions I've started to ask myself is, where is my personal pride getting in the way of my rejoicing or weeping?

14:29.346 --> 14:36.237
Where am I not in this situation counting others more significant than myself?

14:36.257 --> 14:41.045
Do I turn what they're sharing into me an opportunity to talk about me?

14:42.087 --> 14:43.309
What do I say focused on them?

14:43.770 --> 14:44.531
Because here's the deal.

14:44.651 --> 14:51.442
Once we can feel empathy begins to settle in and then we can get close enough to support.

14:52.482 --> 14:55.085
Once you feel, then you're in a place to support.

14:55.386 --> 15:01.653
Dietrich Bonhoeffer said, the truest measure of love is how willingly we enter into another suffering.

15:02.794 --> 15:04.136
It's the truest measure of love.

15:04.657 --> 15:12.666
It's not how someone has to pull us into their suffering, but as soon as we see their suffering, we run into that suffering.

15:12.747 --> 15:15.670
We say, hey, we are here and you are not alone.

15:15.690 --> 15:20.396
And one of the best ways to make sure someone's not alone is make sure the word we exist.

15:21.697 --> 15:22.258
We.

15:22.498 --> 15:26.502
us is so important when it comes to doing ministry.

15:26.603 --> 15:33.050
One Corinthians chapter 12 verse 26 says this, if one member suffers, all suffer what?

15:34.351 --> 15:34.892
Together.

15:34.952 --> 15:36.253
I want to say these words, right?

15:36.634 --> 15:38.776
If one member is honored, all rejoice what?

15:39.697 --> 15:40.918
Together, right?

15:41.279 --> 15:41.999
Together.

15:42.080 --> 15:45.764
If one member suffers, we don't just suffer with them.

15:45.864 --> 15:47.466
We suffer together.

15:47.506 --> 15:51.570
And here's why, because support, close enough to support is a team sport.

15:52.290 --> 15:53.433
It's a team sport.

15:53.473 --> 15:57.484
It takes a village for proximity and empathy to be effective.

15:58.026 --> 16:02.177
We don't have everything that every person will need.

16:02.198 --> 16:05.266
And I believe this is a common stake in the church and in ministry.

16:06.082 --> 16:07.846
It's a common mistake we make in the church.

16:07.946 --> 16:15.041
We start to think at times that the church has the answers that everyone needs and the things that everyone needs.

16:15.141 --> 16:21.976
And then we discount counseling and therapy and medical professionals and all those kinds of things, right?

16:21.996 --> 16:25.042
We think, man, just get them in to a church.

16:25.186 --> 16:29.430
and everything will be fine, but that doesn't, that isn't every person's knees.

16:29.490 --> 16:30.832
They need a group of people.

16:30.852 --> 16:32.293
They need one-to-one friendships.

16:32.553 --> 16:36.718
They may need professionals who have professional thoughts about professional things.

16:37.238 --> 16:39.020
I am not a counselor and a therapist.

16:39.881 --> 16:45.907
I know a lot of scripture and I know a lot about God, but I do not have that training, right?

16:45.927 --> 16:52.914
So I need a village to come alongside me to get close enough.

16:53.218 --> 16:54.120
to support.

16:54.280 --> 17:00.472
And for our church to experience this year of overflow, it's going to take a huge remnant of people.

17:00.853 --> 17:03.438
It won't be the 13 or 12 staff online.

17:03.698 --> 17:04.420
And here's why.

17:04.440 --> 17:11.954
Let me give you a few reasons, a few ways in which all of us need to get close enough to support and how you can support

17:12.066 --> 17:13.367
others in the mission.

17:13.468 --> 17:15.730
First, recognize that we are better together.

17:15.810 --> 17:17.993
We call it in a value of vibrant together.

17:18.033 --> 17:21.596
Here's what 1 Corinthians 12 says about the body of Christ.

17:21.617 --> 17:24.640
For the body does not consist of one member, but of many.

17:25.120 --> 17:25.461
Why?

17:26.582 --> 17:30.847
Why are there many members of the body of Christ and not just one or two members?

17:31.207 --> 17:37.554
Because it takes a village, we're better together to meet the needs of our city.

17:38.914 --> 17:50.432
Some of you, all of you in this room have skills, talents, abilities, training that God wants to use in our city, in our church to help people find and follow Christ.

17:50.592 --> 17:56.921
It is not an accident that you are talented or have a heart for what you have a heart for.

17:57.923 --> 17:58.404
It is not.

17:59.105 --> 18:00.287
But here's what you have to do.

18:00.307 --> 18:02.550
You can't just recognize that you were better together.

18:02.570 --> 18:05.234
You also have to sound your note.

18:06.178 --> 18:07.821
You have to sound your note.

18:07.841 --> 18:11.588
And here's how 1 Corinthians chapter 12 describes it.

18:11.608 --> 18:21.968
It goes on in verse 15 and says, if the foot should say, because I am not a hand, I do not belong to the body, that would not make it any less a part of the body.

18:22.489 --> 18:29.042
The foot may be down there thinking, well, I'm not the hand, so I don't really belong here, but the foot's still a part of the body, whether it likes it or not.

18:30.306 --> 18:34.351
And if the ear should say, because I'm not an eye, I do not belong to the body.

18:34.391 --> 18:37.935
That would not make it any less part of the body.

18:38.596 --> 18:39.196
And here's why.

18:39.256 --> 18:45.764
If the whole body were an ear, where would be the sense, if the whole body were an eye, where would the sense of hearing?

18:45.804 --> 18:48.968
If the whole body were an ear, where would the sense of smell?

18:50.529 --> 18:54.834
So imagine if your foot is like, I hate being a foot.

18:56.817 --> 18:58.098
It's the worst.

18:58.594 --> 18:59.936
We're stuck in shoes all the time.

18:59.976 --> 19:00.817
We smell bad.

19:01.979 --> 19:02.980
Got these ugly nails.

19:03.721 --> 19:05.063
Second toe is bigger than the first.

19:05.103 --> 19:06.445
Like, it's just bad, man.

19:08.307 --> 19:09.469
Got hair on top like a hobbit.

19:11.111 --> 19:11.792
It's just bad.

19:12.292 --> 19:12.813
It's bad.

19:13.033 --> 19:14.095
Need to shave that, by the way.

19:16.558 --> 19:17.860
It says, man, I wish there was a hand.

19:18.681 --> 19:21.405
It's all of a sudden, your foot starts acting like an eyeball.

19:23.327 --> 19:26.812
Now you're jacked, right?

19:26.832 --> 19:28.434
But that's what happens in the church.

19:30.562 --> 19:34.966
Men, I wish I had Brian's voice and presence.

19:34.986 --> 19:36.648
Yeah, me too.

